own literary and artistic works, including films such as Nosferatu, Metropolis, Frankenstein, and Fantasia; the writings of Conrad, Kafka, Goethe, and Novalis; and the paintings of Caspar David Friedrich, one of the leading artists of German Romanticism. With an eye to the modernism of which Weimar filmmaking was a part, The Long Century’s Long Shadow employs the Romantic landscape in poetry and painting as a mirror in which to regard cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aArt and motion pictureszGermany. 0aMotion pictures and literaturezGermany. 0aMotion pictureszGermanyxHistory. 0aMotion pictures, GermanxHistoryy20th century. 0aRomanticismzGermany. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aCaspar David Friedrich.  aGerman romantic art.  aGerman romanticism.  aGoethe.  aNosferatu.  aWeimar cinema.  aabstraction.  aempathy aesthetics.  aexpressionism.  amodernism.  apsychoanalytic approaches to literature and film.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073922040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148752696240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487526962423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487526962/original  a978-3-11-073922-0  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE CO